Step 1: Identify the relevant figures.
• From the Income Statement, the Main Business Revenue (used as credit sales for our purpose) is 7,825,951.24.
• From the Balance Sheet, the Accounts Receivable at the end is 1,988,616.02 and at the beginning is 0.00.

Step 2: Calculate the Average Accounts Receivable.
• Average Accounts Receivable = (Beginning Accounts Receivable + Ending Accounts Receivable) / 2
• = (0 + 1,988,616.02) / 2
• = 994,308.01

Step 3: Calculate the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio.
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Sales (credit sales) / Average Accounts Receivable
• = 7,825,951.24 / 994,308.01
• ≈ 7.87

Thus, the Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio is approximately 7.87.
